-- FACTBOX: Who is giving what in G8 new farm aid initiative
-- 
-- Fri Jul 10, 2009 11:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/10/us-g8-summit-agriculture-aid-factbox-sb-idUSTRE5693J720090710

 

 (Reuters) - The G8 summit in Italy pledged $20 billion of funds over three years to boost agricultural output in poor countries. 

 Following is a list of expected contributions so far from individual countries. * United States: $3.5 billion * Japan: $3 billion * European Union: $1 billion a year until 2011 * France: $2 billion * UK: $1.8 billion * Canada: $520 million * Spain: $500 million * Italy: $450 million (reporting by Reuters correspondents)